The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Vijayan begins new innings
                                                                                                                       7                                      Vijayan begins new innings
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Former India captain I.M. Vijayan, who recently acquired an AFC B license, was unveiled as the coach of IFA Premier Division club Southern Samity, who were promoted last season, at the Rabindra Sarobar Stadium, on Saturday.         
	Vijayan, who has a one-year contract with the club, said that he hoped his stint in Calcutta will help him boost his coaching career.         
	Its an excellent opportunity and I hope that I will be able to do something good here. The most important fact is that I am in the city of football, he said.         
	Speaking about his new assignment, the former striker said he was optimistic that he would be able to deliver the goods with the club. Today (Saturday) was the first day As the training progresses, I hope that everything will come good. Im positive about the assignment, Vijayan said.         
	Vijayan, whose last stint in Calcutta, as a player, was with East Bengal, didnt hide his love for the place.         
	Its really a good feeling to come back here After all, I had been actively involved with soccer in this city in the past, he said.         
	Asked about his future goals, the 41-year-old made it clear that he wanted get an AFC A license. As I have already got the AFC B and C licenses, my next aim is to get the AFC A license.         
	And he didnt stop there as he said that his ultimate aim was to get associated with the national team.                                                                                                                     
